http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: District of Columbia Physical Education Standards

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Regular physical activity is one of the most important ways that individuals maintain and improve their physical health, mental health, and overall well-being. A student who participates in regular physical education is more likely to remain motivated to stay healthy and physically active throughout his or her adult life.. Additionally, the goal is to promote life-long enjoyment and pursuit of physical activity and sports. The physical education standards that follow specify the essential skills and knowledge that all students need in order to build and maintain a healthy life style.
